gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Knicks 126, Spurs 105
gameRecap.excerpt: The Knicks defeated the Spurs, 126-105. Jalen Brunson led all scorers with 25 points (5-8 3PM), along with six assists, while RJ Barrett (24 points, six assists) and Julius Randle (23 points, 16 rebounds, five assists) added a combined 47 points in the victory. Victor Wembanyama tallied 14 points, nine rebounds and two assists for the Spurs in his Madison Square Garden debut. The Knicks improve to 4-4 on the season, while the Spurs fall to 3-5.
